---

==================================================
6. MATHEMATICAL METHODS USED
============================

1. Matrix Addition/Subtraction

* Element-wise operation

2. Matrix Multiplication

* Row × Column multiplication

3. Matrix Division

* A / B = A × B⁻¹

4. Gauss Elimination

* Forward elimination
* Back substitution

5. Gauss Jacobi

* Iterative update using previous values

6. Gauss Seidel

* Iterative update using latest values

7. LU Decomposition

* A = L × U
* Solve using forward + backward substitution

---

==================================================
7. ERROR HANDLING
=================

* Size mismatch → exception
* Non-square matrix → validation
* Non-invertible matrix → error
* File not found → exception

---

==================================================
8. KEY DESIGN DECISIONS
=======================

1. Avoid overengineering

* No unnecessary inheritance

2. Use static methods

* Simpler usage
* Less memory overhead

3. Separate logic into folders

* operations vs solvers

4. Centralized I/O handling

* No duplication

